                <h1>Do Charges Without Conviction Show on Your Record?</h1>
                <p>If you have been charged with a crime but not convicted, it may still appear on your record. The specifics can vary based on jurisdiction and the nature of the charge. Generally, charges that result in a conviction will impact your criminal record, while those that don't may be eligible for expungement or sealing. Consult a legal expert for clarity.</p>
